  "body": "### Description\n\nI am using quarkus platform version: 2.9.2.Final\r\n\r\nI have a use-case where I need to disable the hibernate validation of entities but still be able to control it on demand, in a later step, by using an injected Validator.\r\n\r\nIt seems like this is currently possible only using a persistence.xml file where the property <property name=\"javax.persistence.validation.mode\" value=\"NONE\"/> is set.\r\n\r\nUsing a persistence.xml is a step back and adds some configuration burdens on the project this is why I'd prefer to have a property using which the validation mode could be controlled.\r\n\r\nP.S. I've tried with: quarkus.hibernate-orm.unsupported-properties.\"javax.persistence.validation.mode\"=NONE\r\nbut it still did not work\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nWould be nice to have a hibernate-orm property: **quarkus.hibernate-orm.validation.mode**  that controls how the hibernate validator behaves.",
